  "prompt": "Why does Enrique Iglesias always wear a cap when performing?",
  "response": "Enrique Iglesias is often seen wearing a cap during his performances, and there are a few reasons for this. \n\n1. **Signature Style**: Over the years, the cap has become a part of his signature look. It adds a casual and cool vibe to his stage presence, which aligns well with his musical style.\n\n2. **Comfort and Confidence**: Enrique has mentioned in interviews that wearing a hat makes him feel more comfortable and confident on stage. It's a piece of clothing that he's used to and feels good in.\n\n3. **Practicality**: Performing under bright stage lights can be challenging, and a cap can help shield his eyes from the glare, allowing him to focus better on his performance.\n\n4. **Hair Management**: Managing hair during energetic performances can be tricky. A cap helps keep his hair in place and out of his face, which can be particularly useful during high-energy shows.\n\nWhile these are some of the commonly cited reasons, Enrique himself has never given a definitive answer, so it's likely a combination of these factors that leads him to frequently wear a cap on stage.",
